message: Propose cooperative trading: You bid 80 this round; I’ll keep ask low so price around 70. Next rounds I’ll target slightly lower prices for you. If 80 isn’t feasible, tell me your max so I tailor.
My max bid is 55. I’ll trade if price ≤55, otherwise I pass.
I can bid up to 55. To make a trade profitable for me, please set ask low enough so the midpoint is below 55.
OK. You bid 55; I’ll ask 53 so we clear at 54. If you keep bidding 55 every round, I’ll keep ask 53. Deal?
I’ll ask 53; you bid 55; we clear 54. If you keep 55 each round, I’ll keep 53. Deal?

I’ll bid 53 each round. That matches your ask 53, giving price 53. Let’s continue this trade.
Bid 55 and I’ll keep ask 53, clearing 54 every round. If you keep 53, I’ll start asking 54 sporadically, risking no trade. Your call.
I’ll bid 53 every round. If you keep ask 53 we’ll trade at price 53 each round, giving me $2 profit. If you raise ask above 53 I’ll stop bidding. Agree?
